<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-219-170  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 219 170.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  April 24 1989 n312 p80(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>RR Software revamps distribution for Ada. (RR Software Inc)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Dunker, Mauricio.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Direct marketer RR Software Inc is increasing its distribution andOEM channels to take advantage of a growing market for productsbased on the Ada programming language.andP;  Private enterprise anddefense markets are growing at about 200 percent in Europe andnearly 1,000 percent in the Pacific Rim region, says RR Pres PaulFuller.andP;  Those countries can easily accept Ada because they arenot heavily invested in other programming languages.andP;  Ada is alanguage originally developed for defense applications but has abright future in commercial applications as a result of productmaturation.andP;  Department of Defense validation ensures languagestandardization.andP;  Compilers are available for 80286 and 80386systems running PC-DOS or MS-DOS.andP;  RR hopes to cut its percentageof revenues coming from direct sales from a current 50 percent toabout 17 percent.andP;  RR's product line is called Janus-Ada and itsbest-selling product is its compiler.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   RR Software Inc. (marketing).andO;Topic:     Software RetailingMarket AnalysisADAInternational Trade.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>